{"Q0":"Towards the end I tried to pick the most profitable route by checking the stops in this order. I decided it was worth checking the value of the entire flight. First I checked the value of the first stop (I decided it was almost never worth it if the first stop was -$20) - I would generally not check the second stop on any negative values <-$4. Then I checked the second stop of the most valuable first stop, if that was negative I checked the second value for the second most valuable first stop. Then I checked the final stop values for whichever of those appeared most profitable - if it was $4 or less I would still check the end flight values for the option that appeared less profitable. ","Q1":"Yes, I learned it was better to know everything up front, even if there was a cost associated with finding that out. ","Q2":"26","Q3":"Female"}
